	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Correct. The Super NES checksum appears to have been intended to ensure that the ROM data is not damaged between when it leaves the developer's hard drive and when the first retail cartridges with mask ROMs roll off the production line.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


